Javascript syntax highlighting seems broken in the source viewer, for the following lines:

{code}
var matches = body.match(/name=&#x27;csrfmiddlewaretoken&#x27; value=&#x27;([^&#x27;]+)&#x27;/);
{code}

And

{code}
var downloadLinkMatch = body.match(new RegExp(&#x27;<a href="([^"]+)">&#x27;+filename+&#x27;</a>&#x27;));
{code}

As seen in http://i.imgur.com/sMPuKNl.png line 72 and 113.

I&#x27;m using an example from https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BITBUCKET/OAuth+consumer+examples

Everything seems fine until I try to get only closed issues, so I change

{code}
#!python
url = &#x27;https://bitbucket.org/api/1.0/repositories/%s/%s/issues/&#x27; % (username, repo_slug)
{code}

to

{code}
#!python
url = &#x27;https://bitbucket.org/api/1.0/repositories/%s/%s/issues/?status=closed&#x27; % (username, repo_slug)
{code}

And I get a {{401}} HTTP status. If I change it back - it works fine.

I&#x27;m not able to push to _bitbucket_  with ssh keys.\\
I have added ssh key to my account.\\
{{git push -u origin --all}} gives in following error

{code}
#!BASH

